  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>With RepairQ 1.19.1, we have introduced Catalog Item Quick Create, which allows users to create new catalog items directly from purchase orders and sales/repair tickets.</p><p>There are a few things to remember for Quick Create items:</p><ul><li><p>Items are created at the Global level, i.e., all locations will have access to this catalog item.</p></li><li><p>All roles that have access to creating tickets can quick-create catalog items.</p></li><li><p>Admins can choose which Item Types are used for Quick Create.</p></li></ul><p>Users can add additional columns to the Catalog Item List to see when an item was created and which staff member created it. Users can also filter that list to view items based on which process was used to create the item.</p><h3 id=\"QuickCreate:CatalogItemCreatedContext-InstructionalResources\">Instructional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936261290/Catalog+Quick+Create+Activation\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936261290\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Catalog Quick Create: Activation</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936425167/Quick+Create+Add+New+Catalog+Items+on+Purchase+Orders\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936425167\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Quick Create: Add New Catalog Items on Purchase Orders</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1937015029/Quick+Create+Add+New+Catalog+Items+on+Tickets\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1937015029\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Quick Create: Add New Catalog Items on Tickets</a></p></li></ul><h3 id=\"QuickCreate:CatalogItemCreatedContext-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932329061/Create+a+Catalog+Item\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932329061\" data-linked-resource-version=\"12\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Creating a Catalog Item</a>  </p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932525994/Inventory+Management+Replenishment+Methods\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932525994\" data-linked-resource-version=\"11\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Adding Inventory Into RepairQ</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932427416/Purchase+Order+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932427416\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Purchase Order Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932787772/Merging+Catalog+Items\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932787772\" data-linked-resource-version=\"10\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Merging Catalog Items</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932754986/List+Views\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932754986\" data-linked-resource-version=\"12\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">List Views Overview</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937473555/image-20230607-170751.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"QuickCreate:CatalogItemCreatedContext-AddCreation-RelatedColumnstotheCatalogList\">Add Creation-Related Columns to the Catalog List</h2><p /><p>1. On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Catalog</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937473555/image-20230607-170745.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. On the Catalog Item List screen, click the <strong>Options button (\u22ee)</strong>\u00a0on the right side of the page. From the dropdown list of options, select <strong>Edit Columns</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937473555/image-20230607-170813.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937473555/image-20230607-170839.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3a. Click the <strong>Add Button (+)</strong>, and the Column Edit window will appear. These categories are the current columns on your catalog page.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937473555/image-20230607-170856.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3b. In the category box, type <strong>created</strong>\u00a0and additional column selections will appear.</p><p /><p>3c. Under the Add Columns section, select <strong>Created By, Created From, and Created On </strong>to add them to the column list.</p><p /><p>3d. Once you are finished customizing your category list, click the <strong>Update button (checkmark icon)</strong> to update your list.</p><p /><p>4. After updating the columns, your Catalog Item List will reflect the new categories added.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Created On </strong>- This shows the date when the Catalog Item was created.</p></li><li><p><strong>Created By</strong> - This shows which user created the Catalog Item.</p></li><li><p><strong>Created From </strong>- This shows which process was used to create the Catalog Item.</p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937473555/image-20230607-170911.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p><strong>Note</strong>: You can save this new list view by following the instructions in our Knowledge Base Article, <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932754986/List+Views\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932754986\" data-linked-resource-version=\"12\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">List Views Overview</a>.</p><p /><h2 id=\"QuickCreate:CatalogItemCreatedContext-FiltertheCatalogListbyCreatedContext\">Filter the Catalog List by Created Context</h2><p>When searching the Catalog, there is a new filter named <strong>Created From</strong>. This allows you to search your list based on the created method of the Catalog Item.</p><p class=\"media-group\"><a href=\"/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1937473555/Quick+Create+Catalog+Item+Created+Context?preview=%2F1937473555%2F1983873027%2FInvalid+file+id+-+39e5bbf6-5573-4433-9bac-80aaa2d7ae01\"><span style=\"background: url('/wiki/s/-640127513/6452/0000891dee48b240c5ed2f93f8ac8ad513a32a09/1000.0.0-0000891dee48/_/download/resources/com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-view-file-macro:view-file-macro-resources/images/placeholder-medium-file.png'); width: 250px; height: 95px; display: inline-block; padding-top: 155px; margin: 2px; border: 1px solid #ddd; text-align: center; vertical-align: text-bottom; text-decoration: none; font-size: 12px; color: #000;\">Invalid file id - 39e5bb\u2026</span></a></p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937473555/image-20230607-170944.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><ul><li><p><strong>Catalog Item</strong> - This item was created from the Catalog Item List.</p></li><li><p><strong>Repair Device</strong> - This item was created from a Repair ticket as the assigned repair device.</p></li><li><p><strong>Sale Item</strong> - This item was created from a ticket to sell a product or service.</p></li><li><p><strong>Trade In Item</strong> - This item was created from a Trade In ticket as the assigned trade-in device.</p></li><li><p><strong>Purchase Order Item</strong> - This item was created on a Purchase Order.</p></li></ul><p /><p /><p>START 1.19.X</p>",
